</div><!-- .clearfix -->


  <div class="rfd">
    <div class="nytint-discussion-header">
      <p class="pubdate">July 21, 2014</p>
      <h1>How Can the U.S. Stop Corporate Tax Flight? </h1>
    </div>
  </div><!-- .rfd -->



<div class="rfd nytint-grid-container nytint-extended clearfix">

  <div class="nytint-panelists-rail">
    <div class="nytint-intro">
  <h4 class="nytint-sectionHeader">Introduction</h4>

  <div class="w380 right"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/07/21/opinion/rfdinversion/rfdinversion-sfSpan.jpg" alt="DESCRIPTION" /><span class="caption">Applied Materials and Tokyo Electron, rival chip makers, plan to merge, with the new company moving to the Netherlands to pay less taxes. Gary Dickerson and Tetsuro Higashi are the chief executives.</span> <span class="credit">Alison Yin/A.P. Images, via A.P. Images for Applied Materials</span></div>

<p>In recent months, <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/14/reluctantly-patriot-flees-homeland-to-elude-taxes/">several big U.S. companies</a> have <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/18/abbvie-reaches-deal-to-buy-european-drug-maker-shire/?module=BlogPost-Title&amp;version=Blog%20Main&amp;contentCollection=Mergers%20&amp;%20Acquisitions&amp;action=Click&amp;pgtype=Blogs&amp;region=Body">reached so-called inversion deals</a> that will <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/16/obama-administration-seeks-end-to-inversion-deals/">allow them to reincorporate</a> in countries like Ireland and the Netherlands, where corporate taxes are lower. </p>

<p>Are these deals a sign that corporate taxes should be lowered so American companies can compete on a level playing field with foreign companies, or are they an example of self-serving greed that should be outlawed so companies built with American support pay their fair share?</p>

  
	  <a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/just-one-way-to-stop-corporate-inversions-cut-taxes" class="nytint-enter-discussion">Read the Discussion »</a>
  
</div>
    <div id="MiddleRight" class="ad middle-right-ad marginalia-anchor-ad columnGroup rfd-ad"></div>
  </div><!-- .nytint-panelists-rail -->

  <div class="nytint-discussion-content">

    <h4 class="nytint-sectionHeader">Debaters</h4>

    <ul class="nytint-participants nytint-extended clearfix">

      <li class="  nytint-bylines-1  ">
            	<img alt="Chris Edwards" class="nytint-photo-1" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/03/13/opinion/Chris_Edwards/Chris_Edwards-thumbStandard.jpg" />
        <h3><a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/just-one-way-to-stop-corporate-inversions-cut-taxes">Just One Way to Stop Inversions: Cut Taxes</a></h3>
        <p class="nytint-bylines">
            Chris Edwards, Cato Institute
    		</p>
    		  <p class="nytint-excerpt">Our high tax rate is scaring away investment and reported profits.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="  nytint-bylines-1  ">
            	<img alt="Sander Levin" class="nytint-photo-1" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/07/21/opinion/rfdlevin/rfdlevin-thumbStandard.jpg" />
        <h3><a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/inversions-highlight-unfairness-of-the-tax-code">Inversions Highlight Tax Code Unfairness</a></h3>
        <p class="nytint-bylines">
            Sander Levin, U.S. House of Representatives 
    		</p>
    		  <p class="nytint-excerpt">The wave of corporate inversions threatens to undermine the U.S. tax base and our economy.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="  nytint-bylines-1  ">
            	<img alt="Tim Worstall" class="nytint-photo-1" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/07/21/opinion/rfdworstall/rfdworstall-thumbStandard.jpg" />
        <h3><a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/corporate-taxation-is-inefficient">Corporate Taxation Is Inefficient </a></h3>
        <p class="nytint-bylines">
            Tim Worstall, Adam Smith Institute 
    		</p>
    		  <p class="nytint-excerpt">Taxing economic activity means that we will have less economic activity.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="  nytint-bylines-1  ">
            	<img alt="Chye-Ching Huang" class="nytint-photo-1" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/07/21/opinion/rfdhuang/rfdhuang-thumbStandard.jpg" />
        <h3><a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/end-the-deception-on-profits-and-taxes">End the Deception on Profits and Taxes</a></h3>
        <p class="nytint-bylines">
            Chye-Ching Huang, Center on Budget and Policy Priorities
    		</p>
    		  <p class="nytint-excerpt">By raising U.S. taxes on foreign profits and cutting them on domestic profits, we can level the playing field between companies that use international tax avoidance as a business strategy and those that don’t.</p>
      </li>

      <li class="nytint-last  nytint-bylines-1  ">
            	<img alt="David Cay Johnston" class="nytint-photo-1" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/04/10/opinion/davidcay2/davidcay2-thumbStandard.jpg" />
        <h3><a href="how-can-the-us-stop-corporate-tax-flight/tax-profits-when-earned-to-encourage-investment">Tax Profits When Earned to Encourage Investment </a></h3>
        <p class="nytint-bylines">
            David Cay Johnston, Columnist
    		</p>
    		  <p class="nytint-excerpt">Congress should reform the tax system so that profits are taxed when earned so they can be reinvested in productive ways.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>


  </div><!-- .nytint-discussion-content -->


</div><!-- .nytint-grid-container -->

